This paper deals with fairness in algorithmic decision-making, which is a topic that spans multiple sub-fields in computer science. However, the focus on individual preferences and the optimization of outcomes suggests that machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) are the most likely categories. The paper also touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CR) and social and information networks (cs.SI), as well as the broader topic of computational complexity (cs.CY).
